README.md

Awesome Vagrant

   [https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome]Awesome
   [https://gitter.im/iJackUA/awesome-vagrant?utm_source=badge&utm_medium=
   badge&utm_campaign=pr-badge]Gitter
   [https://travis-ci.org/iJackUA/awesome-vagrant]Build Status

   A curated list of awesome Vagrant resources, plugins, tutorials and
   other nice things.

Official resources

     * [https://www.vagrantup.com/]Vagrant site - installation
       instruction, official manuals and docs.
     * [https://github.com/hashicorp/vagrant]GitHub repo - source code,
       issues discussion and collaboration.

Boxes

   Where to find OS boxes ?
     * [http://www.vagrantbox.es/]Vagrantbox.es - the biggest list of all
       available boxes, maintained by community via GitHub pull requests.
     * [https://app.vagrantup.com/boxes/search]Vagrant Cloud - config
       share, boxes distribution and discovery (also premium features of
       private collaboration and sharing).
     * [https://cloud-images.ubuntu.com/vagrant/]Cloud Images Ubuntu.com -
       "clean" official Ubuntu cloud images.
     * [https://github.com/chef/bento#current-baseboxes]Baseboxes from
       Opscode - CentOS, Fedora, Debian, FreeBSD, Ubuntu.
     * [http://puppet-vagrant-boxes.puppetlabs.com/]Puppet Labs Vagrant
       Boxes - these boxes are provided to be used by various Puppet
       projects.

Provisioning

     * [https://www.vagrantup.com/docs/provisioning/index.html]All
       available build in provisioning providers - official doc.
     * [http://fideloper.github.io/Vaprobash/index.html]Vaprobash -
       Vagrant Provisioning Bash Scripts.

Notable plugins

   You can install these modules by this command vagrant plugin install
   MODULE-NAME
     * [https://github.com/hashicorp/vagrant/wiki/Available-Vagrant-Plugin
       s]List of available Vagrant plugins from GitHub wiki.
     * [https://github.com/dotless-de/vagrant-vbguest]vagrant-vbguest -
       autoupdate VirtualBox guest additions (according to VB version).
     * [https://github.com/cogitatio/vagrant-hostsupdater]vagrant-hostsupd
       ater - adds an entry to your /etc/hosts file on the host system.
     * [http://fgrehm.viewdocs.io/vagrant-cachier/]vagrant-cachier - share
       a common package (apt-get, npm, etc.) cache among similar VM
       instances.
     * [https://github.com/phinze/vagrant-host-shell]vagrant-host-shell -
       a vagrant provisioner to run commands on the host when a VM boots.
     * [https://github.com/jaugustin/vagrant-ansible-local]vagrant-ansible
       -local allow provisioning your VM with ansible playbooks directly
       from the guest VM.
     * [https://github.com/jedi4ever/sahara]sahara - easy manage VM state
       (commit/rollback while experimenting with software stack).
     * [https://github.com/projectatomic/adb-vagrant-registration]vagrant-
       registration - add "register" and "unregister" capabilities to
       Vagrant guests for updates on systems with a subscription
       model(like Red Hat Enterprise Linux).
     * [https://github.com/projectatomic/vagrant-service-manager]vagrant-s
       ervice-manager - enable easier access to the features and services
       provided by the
       [https://github.com/projectatomic/adb-atomic-developer-bundle]Atomi
       c Developer Bundle (ADB).
     * [https://github.com/invernizzi/vagrant-scp]vagrant-scp - Copy files
       to a Vagrant VM via SCP.

Helpers / Tools

     * [https://www.packer.io/]Packer - a tool for creating identical
       machine images for multiple platforms from a single source
       configuration. For fast infrastructure deployment with
       multi-provider portability.
     * [https://github.com/jedi4ever/veewee]Veewee - a tool for easily
       (and repeatedly) building custom Vagrant base boxes, KVMs, and
       virtual machine images.
     * [https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/wiki/Plugins#vagrant]Vag
       rant plugin for ZSH shell - auto-complete for commands, task names,
       box names and built-in documentation.
     * [https://github.com/MunGell/vgm]CLI Vagrant Manager - simple
       command-line tool to manage multiple vagrant boxes

Desktop tools

     * [http://vagrantmanager.com/]Vagrant Manager for OS X.

Web services

   To generate Vagrantfile with automated provisioning scripts.
     * [http://phansible.com/]Phansible - provides an easy to use
       interface that helps you generate Ansible Playbooks for PHP based
       projects.
     * [https://puphpet.com/]PuPHPet - a simple GUI to set up virtual
       machines for [DEL: PHP :DEL] Web development.
     * [http://getprotobox.com/]Protobox - PuPHPet analog, but uses own
       installer with YAML configuration format to control everything that
       is installed on the virtual machine.
     * [http://rove.io/]Rove - a service that allows you to pregenerate
       typical Vagrant builds.

Proxy services

   To proxy your local web server and make it publicly available over the
   internet.
     * [https://www.vagrantup.com/docs/share/]Vagrant share - allows you
       to share your Vagrant environment with anyone in the world.
     * [http://nip.io/]nip.io - a magic domain name that provides wildcard
       DNS for any IP address.
     * [https://ngrok.com/]ngrok - tool to create secure tunnels to expose
       a local server behind a NAT or firewall to the internet.
     * [http://proxylocal.com/]proxylocal.com - proxy your local
       web-server and make it publicly available over the internet.
     * [https://localtunnel.github.io/www/]localtunnel.me - assign you a
       unique publicly accessible url that will proxy all requests to your
       locally running webserver.

Tutorials

     * [http://www.thisprogrammingthing.com/2013/getting-started-with-vagr
       ant/]Getting Started With Vagrant by This Programming Thing.
     * [http://stdout.in/en/post/getting_started_with_vagrant_automated_de
       v_servers_deploy_and_provisioning]Getting started with Vagrant -
       automated dev servers deploy and provisioning.
     * [http://confluence.jetbrains.com/display/PhpStorm/Working+with+Adva
       nced+Vagrant+features+in+PhpStorm]Working with Advanced Vagrant
       features in PhpStorm.
     * [https://scotch.io/tutorials/sharing-your-virtual-machine-on-the-we
       b-with-vagrant-share]Sharing Your Virtual Machine on the Web with
       Vagrant Share.

Books

     * [https://www.amazon.com/Vagrant-Running-Virtualized-Development-Env
       ironments/dp/1449335837]Vagrant: Up and Running by Mitchell
       Hashimoto.
     * [https://leanpub.com/vagrantcookbook]Vagrant CookBook by Erika
       Heidi.

Popular readymade environments

     * [https://github.com/vagrantpress/vagrantpress]Vagrantpress -
       development environment for creating and modifying WordPress sites.
     * [https://github.com/Varying-Vagrant-Vagrants/VVV]Varying Vagrant
       Vagrants - An open source Vagrant configuration focused on
       WordPress development.
     * [https://github.com/joomlatools/joomlatools-vagrant]Joomla-Vagrant.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/vdd]VDD - Vagrant Drupal
       Development.
     * [https://www.drupalvm.com/]Drupal VM - A VM for local Drupal
       development, built with Vagrant + Ansible
     * [https://github.com/iJackUA/try-yii2]Try Yii2 - try Yii2 with
       Vagrant VM + Ansible provisioning = Complete readymade virtual
       server playground.
     * [https://github.com/bryannielsen/Laravel4-Vagrant]Laravel4-Vagrant
       - run Laravel 4 inside a Ubuntu 12.04 Vagrant Virtual Machine w/PHP
       5.5.
     * [https://github.com/openstack-ansible/openstack-ansible]OpenStack
       on Ansible with Vagrant.
     * [https://laravel.com/docs/master/homestead]Laravel Homestead -
       Official Vagrant Box for Laravel development, based on Ubuntu 16.04
       LTS, PHP 7, Nginx, and multiple database platforms.
     * [https://scotch.io/bar-talk/announcing-scotch-box-2-0-our-dead-simp
       le-vagrant-lamp-stack-improved]Scotch Box - Simple Vagrant Box with
       [https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/LAMP_%28software_bundle%29]LAMP
       stack, plus some useful extras, based on Ubuntu 14.04 LTS.

